      • Serialized Fields

        • perday

          int perday
          Number of times this spell can be cast before needing to rest. A maximum of 5 is enforced since in the Challenging Challenge Ratings document more than 5 casts per day represent the same CR.

        • used

          int used
          Number of spent uses.

        • castoutofbattle

          boolean castoutofbattle
          Set to true if can be cast outside of battle.

        • castinbattle

          boolean castinbattle
          Set to true if can be used during combat.

        • castonallies

          boolean castonallies
          Set to true if able to target allies.

        • automatichit

          boolean automatichit
          Set to true if doesn't need to roll a touch attack.
          See Also:
          Spell.hit(Combatant, Combatant, BattleState)

        • isritual

          boolean isritual
          Rituals are cast by NPCs in Shrines.

        • isscroll

          boolean isscroll
          true if can automatically generate a Scroll for this.

        • ispotion

          boolean ispotion
          Same as Spell.isscroll but for Potions.

        • iswand

          boolean iswand
          Same as Spell.isscroll but for Wands.

        • provokeaoo

          boolean provokeaoo
          If false will not consider this threatening (ignores attacks of opportunity so it can be cast while engaged without needing a Skills.concentration roll). Default: true.

        • apcost

          float apcost
          How many action points to spend when casting (default: standard action).

        • casterlevel

          java.lang.Integer casterlevel
          Level this spell is being cast at.

        • level

          int level
          Spell level.

        • cr

          float cr
          TODO Only ChallengeRatingCalculator and CrFactor system should know about this stuff.

        • components

          int components
          Material components cost.

        • realm

          Realm realm
          Used to determine where each Scroll will be sold.

A value of null means that the hand is initially empty, that it's card has been spent or that there are no more valid cards of that type. These are the card types by index for non-hostile (human) Towns: 0 - Grow 1 - Native (from #realm) Upgrade. 2 - Foreign Upgrade 3 - Native Item. 4 - Foreign Item 5 - Native Monster lair, see #lairs 6 - Special card 7 - Accommodations upgrade. 8 - Transport upgrade. These are the card types by index for hostile (monster) Towns: 0 - Grow 1 - Native Monster lair, see #lairs 2-7 - RecruitOption for it to recruit an unit into Location.garrison
          See Also:
          Research.draw(Town)

        • queue

          ResearchQueue queue
          See Also:
          ResearchQueue

      • Serialized Fields

        • WINMESSAGES

          java.lang.String[] WINMESSAGES
          A curiosity: I had no intention of having seven different types of Keys in the game - they were a late 1.1 idea to give more of a long-term goal to the game. Fuck, I didn't even plan for Towns to have any sort of theme at all - they were just supposed to be random collections of upgrades and items that eventually got too big to be purely random (or it would be a pain in the ass to keep track of what is where in each game) - but in the end is there anything more win than Helloween? So I had to make the best out of this coincidence :)
